1. Healthy Beef from Whisky Country 13th October 2015: An on-farm discussion on the prevention and control of cryptosporidium in beef herds to farmers in the North East of Scotland held on the Glenlivet Estate followed by a lunch and panel discussion at the Glenlivet distillery. This event was put together by Moredun colleagues on this project in collaboration with the Crown Estates, High-Health scheme in Orkney and the local veterinary practices.
2. Prevention and Control of cryptosporidiosis in cattle: 10th November 2015: An evening discussion at Dunster town hall in Somerset, organised by Moredun colleagues on the project.
